  "description": "<i>Tetriz</i> is a <i><a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?platform=Amiga\">Tetris</a></i> clone, written in Oberon language with the aims of being small (6 kB) and running in a window. The game is controlled via the numerical keypad and comes in three variations: <i>Tetriz, MegaTetriz</i> and <i>MiniTetriz</i>. The plain version has the same width as most <i>Tetris</i> variants, whereas <i>MegaTetriz</i> runs in a roughly 2½ times wider window. <i>MiniTetriz</i> is only four blocks wide, giving a new dimension to gameplay.<br><br><i>Tetriz</i> was later adapted to run in a text window, under the title of <i>Contris</i>, which also saw use as a BBS door.",
